        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(voice-call): require realtime websocket path boundary",
        "body": "Summary:\n- Tightens realtime voice WebSocket upgrade routing so same-prefix sibling paths are not routed to the realtime handler.\n- Previously, `/voice/stream/realtime-evil/token` matched `/voice/stream/realtime` because the matcher used raw `startsWith(pattern)` matching.\n- The matcher now accepts only the exact configured path or a real slash-delimited child path under it.\n- Preserves the existing root `realtime.streamPath=\"/\"` behavior so root child paths such as `/token` still route to the realtime handler.\n- Keeps the regression proof in `extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts`, exercising the real `VoiceCallWebhookServer` upgrade listener rather than a private matcher.\n\nValidation:\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts`\n  - 42 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts`\n  - 61 passed\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts`\n  - passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts`\n  - passed\n- `git diff --check`\n  - passed\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Realtime voice WebSocket upgrade routing accepted same-prefix sibling paths such as `/voice/stream/realtime-evil/token` for a configured realtime stream path of `/voice/stream/realtime`.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS with Node, running the real `VoiceCallWebhookServer` on an ephemeral localhost TCP port through the webhook regression harness.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts`\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output from the post-fix local run showed the webhook regression file passing against the real bound server path, including the realtime WebSocket upgrade routing cases:\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts\n\nextensions/voice-call/src/webhook.test.ts\n  VoiceCallWebhookServer realtime WebSocket routing\n    ✓ does not route sibling paths through the realtime stream handler\n    ✓ routes root stream child paths through the realtime stream handler\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       42 passed (42)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: `/voice/stream/realtime/token` reached the realtime handler and returned the test handler's 401 response. `/voice/stream/realtime-extra/token` did not increase the realtime handler call count. With `realtime.streamPath=\"/\"`, `/token` still reached the realtime handler.\n\nWhat was not tested: External telephony-provider infrastructure and remote reverse-proxy ingress were not exercised; this proof is limited to the local OpenClaw webhook server route boundary and WebSocket upgrade dispatch.\n",
        "branch": "fix/voice-call-realtime-ws-path-boundary",
